  "_comment_restaurant": "Below: the Restaurant map catalog. Each entry keeps a primitive shape (box/cylinder/cone/sphere + color) as a FALLBACK and a size target, and adds a `model` path (relative to /assets/) to the real Kay Lousberg 'Restaurant Bits' GLB (CC0). scene.js loads the GLB lazily at match start and swaps it in over the primitive; if the GLB is missing or fails to load, the primitive is used for that one item. Only clean model names are referenced (never the fetch's hash-suffixed duplicates).",

  "_comment_props": "--- Disguise PROPS: genuinely small / movable items only (chairs, stools, crates, cookware, dishes, food). These are the disguise pool the referee builds from map.props. A fixture must NEVER appear here. Primitive dims for MEASURED items = native x 0.75 (the restaurant map.modelScale), so the collider and the primitive fallback match the drawn GLB; the disguise is worn at the same 0.75 scale (scene.meshForPlayer) so a player hidden as a burger is burger-sized, not player-sized. Unmeasured small food/cookware keep proportionate estimates and inherit the 0.75 visual scale.",
